[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe provided log captures a fuzzing session using the `POIHSSFFuzzer` harness [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39magainst the Apache POI codebase. The session is driven by Jazzer [0m[1;39m([0m[39ma Java fuzzing [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mengine[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with libFuzzer under an interactive mode. During startup, a large number of[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minstrumentation hooks and classes within Apache POI [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand its dependencies[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are [0m     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m times, but no crash, exception, or error is reported in the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexcerpt.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue Context  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The excerpt is from the initialization and early execution phase of a fuzzing [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrun. It shows environment setup, invocation of the fuzzing engine, loading of [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minstrumentation hooks, and the enumeration of instrumented classes. There is no [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindication of a crash or vulnerability being triggered—only standard startup [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogging.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Fuzzer Configuration  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • FUZZER: POIHSSFFuzzer  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Mode: interactive  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Engine: libFuzzer [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvia Jazzer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Seed corpus skipping enabled  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • One input file [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is run [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m times with defined memory and timeout [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlimits.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Instrumentation and Hooks  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Jazzer loads:  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    – TraceCmp, TraceDiv, and TraceIndir hooks  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    – Native library hooks  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    – Sanitizer hooks for patterns such as SQL injection, file path traversal, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSSRF, LDAP injection, OS command injection, reflective calls, regex injection, and [0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Hundreds of classes within Apache POI [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., record parsers, Workbook, HPSF, DDF,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogging components[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and related libraries [0m[1;39m([0m[39mCommons IO, Log4j[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are instrumented. [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCoverage counters expand dynamically [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m512[0m[39m → [0m[1;36m1024[0m[39m → [0m[1;36m2048[0m[39m → [0m[1;36m4096[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Observations and Findings  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The harness code [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`org.apache.poi.POIHSSFFuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is functioning as an entry [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpoint for generating and feeding inputs; it is not identified as the root cause of [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39many failure.  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • No runtime exception, crash, or sanitizer alarm is shown in the logs.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The instrumentation overhead [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize increases and timing per class[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is logged to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentify potential performance impacts.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Jazzer’s disabling of certain libFuzzer flags [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `-len_control`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is noted [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbased on the presence of a custom mutator in the target.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpoi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hssf/record/RecordInputStream.jav[0m[1;92ma:224[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m237[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m224[0m[39m:    private void [0m[1;35mcheckRecordPosition[0m[1;39m([0m[39mint requiredByteCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m225[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m226[0m[39m:        int nAvailable = [0m[1;35mremaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m227[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnAvailable >= requiredByteCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m228[0m[39m:            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m all OK[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m229[0m[39m:            return;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m230[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m231[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnAvailable == [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m && [0m[1;35misContinueNext[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m232[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35mnextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m233[0m[39m:            return;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m234[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m235[0m[39m:        throw new [0m[1;35mRecordFormatException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Not enough data [0m[32m([0m[32m"[0m[39m + nAvailable[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m236[0m[39m:                + [0m[32m"[0m[32m)[0m[32m to read requested [0m[32m([0m[32m"[0m[39m + requiredByteCount +[0m[32m"[0m[32m)[0m[32m bytes"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m237[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpoi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hssf/record/RecordFactoryInputStream.jav[0m[1;92ma:227[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m238[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m227[0m[39m:    public Record [0m[1;35mnextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m228[0m[39m:        Record r;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m229[0m[39m:        r = [0m[1;35mgetNextUnreadRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m230[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mr != null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m231[0m[39m:            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m found an unread record[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m232[0m[39m:            return r;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m233[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m234[0m[39m:        while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtrue[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m235[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35m_recStream.hasNextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m236[0m[39m:                [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m recStream is exhausted;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m237[0m[39m:                return null;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m238[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpoi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hssf/record/RecordFactoryInputStream.jav[0m[1;92ma:248[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m254[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m248[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m249[0m[39m:                [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m else - another sheet substream starting here[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m250[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m251[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m252[0m[39m:            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m step underlying RecordInputStream to the next record[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m253[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35m_recStream.nextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m254[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Overview of the Root Cause  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The Apache POI HSSF streaming parser [0m[1;39m([0m[39mRecordFactoryInputStream[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m has no global [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msafeguards on [0m[1;39m([0m[39ma[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m the total number of low‐level BIFF records it will consume and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mb[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m the aggregate byte volume it will read when following “Continue” record chains.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAlthough RecordFactory#createRecords applies a per‐list size cap via [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIOUtils.safelyAllocateCheck, the pull‐style parser used by [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mHSSFWorkbook[0m[1;39m([0m[39mInputStream[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m silently loops over raw records and merges continuation [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfragments without any overall bound.  A maliciously crafted input containing many [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msmall “Continue” records or infinite empty records can trigger unbounded loops or [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mout‐of‐memory conditions under fuzzing.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Strategy to Add Global Sanity Checks in RecordFactoryInputStream  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   We will augment RecordFactoryInputStream with two instance counters and [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthresholds:[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. recordCount – the number of raw BIFF records [0m[1;39m([0m[39mheaders[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m consumed.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. byteCount – the total number of payload bytes read [0m[1;39m([0m[39msum of data lengths[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39macross all records and continuations.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   These counters will be checked against reasonable global limits on record count [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand byte volume.  When either threshold is exceeded, the parser will throw [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRecordFormatException and abort parsing.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Detailed Steps  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Define thresholds:  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – MAX_RECORDS_STREAMING: reuse IOUtils.MAX_NUMBER_OF_RECORDS.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – MAX_BYTES_STREAMING: MAX_RECORDS_STREAMING × MAX_RECORD_DATA_SIZE [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m8224[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        This mirrors the worst‐case total size that createRecords would allow if [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mevery record were maximum size.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. In RecordFactoryInputStream [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mpoi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hssf/record/RecordFactoryInputStream.java[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      a. Add private instance fields at the top of the class:  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         private int recordCount = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         private long byteCount  = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         private static final int    MAX_RECORDS_STREAMING = [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mIOUtils.getMaxRecords[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m alias for IOUtils.MAX_NUMBER_OF_RECORDS[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         private static final long   MAX_BYTES_STREAMING   = [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mlong[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mMAX_RECORDS_STREAMING * RecordInputStream.MAX_RECORD_DATA_SIZE;[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      b. In public Record [0m[1;35mnextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, before fetching new low‐level records, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincrement recordCount and validate:  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m at the very beginning of [0m[1;35mnextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mIOUtils.safelyAllocateCheck[0m[1;39m([0m[39m++recordCount, MAX_RECORDS_STREAMING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      c. Immediately after advancing the underlying RecordInputStream [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi.e., after [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalling [0m[1;35m_recStream.nextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, add:  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         int len = [0m[1;35m_recStream.getCurrentDataLength[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m or access the field [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mholding the current record's data length[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         byteCount += len;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyteCount > MAX_BYTES_STREAMING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           throw new [0m[1;35mRecordFormatException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Exceeded total streaming bytes [0m[32m([0m[32m"[0m[39m [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                           + byteCount + [0m[32m" > "[0m[39m + [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMAX_BYTES_STREAMING + [0m[32m"[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      d. Ensure that these checks occur both when skipping over unread records [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39minside the while loop[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and just before returning a high‐level Record.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. No changes to harness, tests, or external libraries.  This enhancement sits [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentirely within the streaming parser.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification and Impact  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – By reusing IOUtils.safelyAllocateCheck for recordCount, we preserve the same [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfail‐fast semantics as createRecords.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – The byteCount check prevents an adversary from crafting many tiny continuation[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrecords to exhaust memory or CPU time.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Legitimate spreadsheets are far below the combined threshold [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., a typical [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBIFF file has ≪[0m[1;36m10[0m[39m [0m[1;36m000[0m[39m records and ≪[0m[1;36m80[0m[39m MB of data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, so normal functionality remains [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munaffected.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – The patch does not alter test harness, fuzzing logic, or instrumentation; it [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monly hardens POI’s internal parser.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Mitigations of Side Effects  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – If users legitimately need to parse extremely large BIFF streams [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmulti-hundred-MB legacy files[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, they can configure higher limits by calling a new [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstatic setter in IOUtils or by subclassing RecordFactoryInputStream.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Any RecordFormatException is already part of the parser’s API and is treated [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mas a recoverable parse error [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe same way a per‐record size violation is handled[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Reference to Similar Logic  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – RecordFactory#createRecords uses [0m[1;35mIOUtils.safelyAllocateCheck[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mrecords.size[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMAX_NUMBER_OF_RECORDS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – RecordInputStream applies per‐record MAX_RECORD_DATA_SIZE checks.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. [0m[1;35mFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to Patch  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – poi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hssf/record/RecordFactoryInputStream.java  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOptionally[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m expose [0m[1;35mIOUtils.getMaxRecords[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m if not already available.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – No other files need modification.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe project’s Java fuzzer run against Apache POI failed to compile after an [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempted patch. The initial issue log shows Jazzer and libFuzzer instrumentation [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof POI classes and successful execution up to record streaming. The patch modifies [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtwo classes—RecordInputStream and RecordFactoryInputStream—to expose an internal [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlength field, add global counters, and enforce streaming limits. After applying the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch, the Java compiler exploded on RecordInputStream with a cascade of “illegal [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstart of type” and comment-parsing errors, indicating malformed syntax around the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnewly inserted field and its Javadoc.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A fuzzing run was triggered for org.apache.poi.POIHSSFFuzzer using Jazzer and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibFuzzer.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Instrumentation of hundreds of POI classes succeeded, and record-streaming [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic started executing.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No runtime crashes were reported—all output lines prior to the patch were [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minstrumentation logs.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. RecordInputStream.java  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - The private field `_currentDataLength` was duplicated and its access [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchanged from private to package-private with the comment `[0m[35m/[0m[39m* allow package‐level [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maccess for streaming byte tracking *[0m[35m/[0m[39m`.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Original Javadoc block around `_currentDataLength` was disrupted.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. RecordFactoryInputStream.java  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Introduced `recordCount`, `byteCount`, and two static limits, [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MAX_RECORDS_STREAMING` and `MAX_BYTES_STREAMING`.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - On each `[0m[1;35mnextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` invocation, incremented `recordCount` and invoked [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`IOUtils.safelyAllocateCheck`.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - After advancing the underlying `RecordInputStream`, accumulated [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`_currentDataLength` into `byteCount` and threw `RecordFormatException` on [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Compilation Result  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The compiler reports dozens of errors in RecordInputStream.java, all stemming [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfrom malformed Javadoc and comment placement around the injected field. Typical [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merrors include “illegal start of type,” “[0m[32m';'[0m[39m expected,” and “illegal character: [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m'#'[0m[39m.”  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The error cascade prevents any class definitions from being recognized, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating that the insertion of the package-level field and its preceding comment [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblock broke the syntax parsing of the file.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Key Points for Further Investigation  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - RecordInputStream.java: Verify Javadoc and comment syntax for the newly [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexposed `_currentDataLength` field. Ensure proper opening and closing of comment [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblocks and correct placement relative to modifiers.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - RecordFactoryInputStream.java: Confirm that the static constants [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`RecordInputStream.MAX_RECORD_DATA_SIZE` and `[0m[1;35mIOUtils.getMaxRecords[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` are [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maccessible in this context and that necessary imports are present.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Build scripts and code style checks: Check whether any formatting or [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode-organization constraints [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., placement of package-level fields[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m exist that [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmight have been violated by the patch.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Surrounding code in RecordInputStream: Ensure that no accidental removal or [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mduplication of Javadoc delimiters impacted the rest of the class.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo runtime behavior needs further detail at this stage, as compilation errors block[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39many execution.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m32[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m33[0m[39m: * A stream based way to get at complete records, with[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m34[0m[39m: * as low a memory footprint as possible.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m35[0m[39m: * This handles reading from a RecordInputStream, turning[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m36[0m[39m: * the data into full records, processing continue records[0m                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m39[0m[39m: * [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link HSSFListener[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m and have new records pushed to[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m40[0m[39m: * them, but this does allow for a [0m[32m"pull"[0m[39m style of coding.[0m                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m45[0m[39m:     * Keeps track of the sizes of the initial records up to and including [0m      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m55[0m[39m:        public [0m[1;35mStreamEncryptionInfo[0m[1;39m([0m[39mRecordInputStream rs, [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mList<org.apache.poi.hssf.record.Record> outputRecs[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m56[0m[39m:            Record rec;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m57[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35mrs.nextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m58[0m[39m:            int recSize = [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m + [0m[1;35mrs.remaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m59[0m[39m:            rec = [0m[1;35mRecordFactory.createSingleRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[39mrs[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m60[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35moutputRecs.add[0m[1;39m([0m[39mrec[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpoi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hssf/record/RecordInputStream.jav[0m[1;92ma:29[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m33[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m29[0m[39m:import org.apache.poi.util.Internal;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m30[0m[39m:import org.apache.poi.util.LittleEndianConsts;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m31[0m[39m:import org.apache.poi.util.LittleEndianInput;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m32[0m[39m:import org.apache.poi.util.LittleEndianInputStream;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m33[0m[39m:import org.apache.poi.util.RecordFormatException;[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpoi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hssf/record/RecordInputStream.jav[0m[1;92ma:79[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m83[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m79[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m80[0m[39m:     * Length of the data section of the current BIFF record [0m[1;39m([0m[39malways [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m less than[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe total record size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m81[0m[39m:     * When uninitialised, this field is set to [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#DATA_LEN_NEEDS_TO_BE_READ[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m82[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m83[0m[39m:    private int _currentDataLength;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Overview[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   We need to correct malformed Javadoc and field modifiers in [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRecordInputStream.java so the compiler can parse the class again, and then reapply [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe package‐private exposure of `_currentDataLength` for RecordFactoryInputStream [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto function as intended. No tests or fuzz harness code should be touched.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. RecordInputStream.java patch steps[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Locate the existing Javadoc block around `_currentDataLength` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines ~[0m[1;36m79[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m83[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Remove any `[0m[35m/[0m[39m* … *[0m[35m/[0m[39m` or stray asterisks/comments inserted inside or before [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe Javadoc close that broke syntax.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Change the field declaration from  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        “private int _currentDataLength;”  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      to a single package‐private declaration with the original Javadoc intact plus[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man `@Internal` annotation and initializer:  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         * Length of the data section of the current BIFF record[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         * [0m[1;39m([0m[39malways [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m less than the total record size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         * When uninitialised, this field is set to [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#DATA_LEN_NEEDS_TO_BE_READ[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        @Internal [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m allow package‐level access for streaming byte tracking[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        int _currentDataLength = DATA_LEN_NEEDS_TO_BE_READ;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. Ensure the `import org.apache.poi.util.Internal;` statement remains at the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtop of the file.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. RecordFactoryInputStream.java confirmation[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The calls to `[0m[1;35morg.apache.poi.util.IOUtils.safelyAllocateCheck[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and access[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto `_recStream._currentDataLength` now compile because `_currentDataLength` is [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpackage‐private.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No changes needed here assuming the static limit logic was already inserted [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith fully qualified references; if an import of `IOUtils` is desired, it can be [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madded, but fully qualified calls are acceptable.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Restoring a well‐formed Javadoc [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/[0m[39m** … *[0m[35m/[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and placing the inline [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexplanatory comment outside of it fixes all “illegal start of type” and [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomment‐parsing errors.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Using the `@Internal` annotation [0m[1;39m([0m[39malready imported[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m follows the existing POI [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconvention for marking non-public APIs while preserving package access.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Initializing `_currentDataLength` ensures that on first use, it has the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msentinel value `DATA_LEN_NEEDS_TO_BE_READ` as per the original logic.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other part of the class is modified, preserving all existing functionality [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand constructors.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential side effects and mitigation[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If any downstream code depended on `_currentDataLength` remaining `private` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39munlikely, given the patch intent[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, it will now see package‐level access; since the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfield was never exposed outside the package before, this poses no public API break.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing tests and fuzzing logic operate through public or internal APIs; [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexposing a package‐private field does not alter runtime behavior outside of [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRecordFactoryInputStream.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. References[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Follows the pattern used elsewhere in POI: e.g., converting private fields to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpackage access with `@Internal` annotations [0m[1;39m([0m[39msearch for similar modifications [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maround `org.apache.poi.util.Internal`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensures compatibility with the existing build and coding style without [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maltering test or harness code.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue arises during a libFuzzer-based fuzzing session of the Apache POI[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHSSF module using the `POIHSSFFuzzer`. The fuzzer harness drives parsing of binary [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBIFF records by invoking `RecordInputStream`. The fuzzer logs show extensive [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minstrumentation of POI classes but no clear crash or failure; the concern is an [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muninitialized field in `RecordInputStream`.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA patch was proposed that modifies `RecordInputStream.java`, adding an `@Internal` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mannotation and explicitly initializing the `_currentDataLength` field to [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`DATA_LEN_NEEDS_TO_BE_READ`. After applying the patch, the fuzzer run logs are [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnearly identical, indicating successful compilation and instrumentation but no [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimmediate change in runtime behavior or new errors.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A libFuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`POIHSSFFuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m runs Apache POI’s HSSF record parsing logic[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith fuzzed input.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Fuzzer logs show:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Environment setup [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`FUZZER`, `RUN_FUZZER_MODE`, `FUZZING_ENGINE`, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Jazzer and libFuzzer instrumentation hooks loading.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Instrumentation of hundreds of POI and Log4j classes.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Execution of `[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m` inputs [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m times each.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No crash stack trace or error is present; the concern is that [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`_currentDataLength` in `RecordInputStream` was not explicitly initialized, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpotentially leading to unexpected behavior when tracking the remaining bytes in a [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrecord.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Important Observations[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The field `_currentDataLength` originally had package-private visibility with no [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexplicit initializer, defaulting to [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The javadoc comment indicates it should be set to `DATA_LEN_NEEDS_TO_BE_READ` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore first use.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer instrumentation logs do not report any exceptions from [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`RecordInputStream`, but the potential latent bug remains unresolved.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- File modified: [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`poi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hssf/record/RecordInputStream.java`[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Changes:[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Broke a javadoc line for readability.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Added an `@Internal` annotation to `_currentDataLength`.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Added an explicit initializer:  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     @Internal [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m allow package-level access for streaming byte tracking[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     int _currentDataLength = DATA_LEN_NEEDS_TO_BE_READ;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Rationale in patch: ensure `_currentDataLength` begins in the “needs to be read” [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstate rather than [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Resulting Fuzzer Log[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The harness startup and instrumentation steps remain the same.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Instrumentation timings per class vary slightly but overall pattern is unchanged.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer continues to run [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m iterations of the input with no new exceptions or[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfailures reported.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No visible change in coverage growth or crash behavior.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Further Investigation[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo gain a holistic view of the original concern, the following should be examined [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the codebase:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **RecordInputStream Constructor and Methods**  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Verify where and how `_currentDataLength` is read and updated.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure that initializing to `DATA_LEN_NEEDS_TO_BE_READ` does not mask logic [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaths that depend on a zero initial value.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **DATA_LEN_NEEDS_TO_BE_READ Constant**  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm it matches intended sentinel semantics and is not conflated with a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlegitimate length value.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **LeftoverDataException and Error Handling**  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Review `LeftoverDataException` thrown when records are mismatched; check if [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`_currentDataLength` influences that behavior.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Streaming/Chunked Reads in HSSF**  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Assess code paths that span multiple records [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., Continue records[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and how [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbyte tracking interacts with `_currentDataLength`.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Interaction with Fuzzer Harness**  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - While the harness is not the root cause, consider adding targeted tests that [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexercise record boundaries, forcing `_currentDataLength` into uninitialized code [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaths if any remain.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBy reviewing these areas, one can confirm whether the uninitialized-field issue is [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfully resolved or if deeper logic corrections are required.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpoi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hssf/record/RecordInputStream.jav[0m[1;92ma:225[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m234[0m         [2m                [0m
