[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m234[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpoi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hssf/record/RecordInputStream.jav[0m[1;92ma:255[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m264[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m255[0m[39m:        _currentDataOffset += LittleEndianConsts.SHORT_SIZE;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m256[0m[39m:        return [0m[1;35m_dataInput.readShort[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m257[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m258[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m259[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m260[0m[39m:     * Reads a [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m bit, signed value[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m261[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m262[0m[39m:    @Override[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m263[0m[39m:    public int [0m[1;35mreadInt[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m264[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mcheckRecordPosition[0m[1;39m([0m[39mLittleEndianConsts.INT_SIZE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpoi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hssf/record/RecordInputStream.jav[0m[1;92ma:57[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m63[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m57[0m[39m:    public static final class LeftoverDataException extends RuntimeException [0m[1;39m{[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m58[0m[39m:        public [0m[1;35mLeftoverDataException[0m[1;39m([0m[39mint sid, int remainingByteCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m59[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35msuper[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Initialisation of record 0x"[0m[39m + [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mInteger.toHexString[0m[1;39m([0m[39msid[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toUpperCase[0m[1;39m([0m[39mLocale.ROOT[0m[1;39m)[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m60[0m[39m:                    + [0m[32m"[0m[32m([0m[32m"[0m[39m + [0m[1;35mgetRecordName[0m[1;39m([0m[39msid[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[32m"[0m[32m)[0m[32m left "[0m[39m + remainingByteCount[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m61[0m[39m:                    + [0m[32m" bytes remaining still to be read."[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m62[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m63[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Revert the field-level initializer and annotation:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Change  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     `@Internal int _currentDataLength = DATA_LEN_NEEDS_TO_BE_READ;`  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     back to  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     `private int _currentDataLength;`  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     This ensures the old semantics of default‐zero apply until the constructor [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprimes the first record.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Prime the first record in the constructor:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After `_nextSid = [0m[1;35mreadNextSid[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` in the `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mInputStream, EncryptionInfo, int[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstructor, immediately call `[0m[1;35mnextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       _nextSid = [0m[1;35mreadNextSid[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m PRIME FIRST RECORD[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m_nextSid != INVALID_SID_VALUE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m sets _currentSid, _currentDataLength, _currentDataOffset[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;35mnextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This guarantees that from the moment a RecordInputStream is instantiated, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`_currentDataLength` and `_currentSid` reflect a real record, not a sentinel.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Adjust [0m[1;35mavailable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to never return negative:[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Modify `public int [0m[1;35mavailable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to guard against the sentinel:[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       @Override[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       public int [0m[1;35mavailable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m_currentDataLength == DATA_LEN_NEEDS_TO_BE_READ[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m before any [0m[1;35mnextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: no data ready to read[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m after priming or [0m[1;35mreadNextSid[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           return [0m[1;35mremaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This avoids negative [0m[1;35mavailable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand negative chunk sizes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when methods are [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minadvertently called before reading the first record.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Update [0m[1;35mhasNextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m logic to account for the new priming:[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Since we now automatically advance into the first record, change [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mhasNextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to only look ahead:[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       public boolean [0m[1;35mhasNextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m if still within current record, disallow hasNextRecord misuse[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m_currentDataLength != DATA_LEN_NEEDS_TO_BE_READ && [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m_currentDataLength != _currentDataOffset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               throw new [0m[1;35mLeftoverDataException[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m readNextSid only when _nextSid not yet set to EOF[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m_nextSid == INVALID_SID_VALUE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               return false;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           return true;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By decoupling sentinel state from [0m[1;35mhasNextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, we make the loop simple:[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       while [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35min.hasNextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m current record already primed[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;35mprocessRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[39min[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m prepare for next[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           if [0m[1;39m([0m[39min._nextSid != INVALID_SID_VALUE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m[1;35mnextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               break;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Add targeted unit tests [0m[1;39m([0m[39min `poi/src/test/java/[0m[33m...[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that:[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Instantiate a `RecordInputStream` on a BIFF stream containing a single record,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthen assert:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - `[0m[1;35mavailable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` returns the record’s data-length immediately after [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstruction.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - `[0m[1;35mgetSid[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;35mreadByte[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;35mreadShort[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` work without a prior explicit [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mnextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` call.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - `[0m[1;35mhasNextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` returns false after reading the only record.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Construct a zero-byte input, asserting that the constructor or [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mhasNextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` immediately returns false without throwing.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Regression and Side-Effect Mitigations:[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Removing the explicit initializer restores the pre-patch behavior for any code[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat might have invoked `[0m[1;35mavailable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` or `[0m[1;35mreadFully[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` before the first record.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Automatic priming prevents negative or zero-length‐sentinel visibility to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcallers, making downstream code simpler.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing tests for multi-record and “continue”‐record handling will remain [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalid, since `[0m[1;35mnextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is still used internally to advance between records.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No changes occur to harness code, fuzzing logic, or external libraries.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRationale:[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The original patch only added an initializer but did not change the code paths [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat actually set `_currentDataLength`. Since the constructor already calls [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mreadNextSid[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, the field was never truly “uninitialized,” and the patch had no [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meffect on runtime behavior.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Negative `[0m[1;35mavailable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` results and the need for callers always to invoke [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mnextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` can be error-prone. By priming the first record in the constructor, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwe guarantee that from the outset the internal state is consistent [0m[1;39m([0m[39m_Sid, [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m_currentDataLength, _currentDataOffset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, removing latent pitfalls.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This approach preserves all existing logic for reading BIFF records, including [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmulti‐chunk “Continue” records, `LeftoverDataException` checks, and boundary [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidations, while preventing any negative-remaining or uninitialized‐field [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mscenarios.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO: Instrumented org.apache.logging.log4j.util.Cast with custom hooks only [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtook [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m0[0m[39m ms, size +[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m%[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO: Instrumented[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [33m...[0m[39m [0m[1;39m[[0m[39mTRUNCATED[0m[1;39m][0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn Apache POI HSSF fuzzer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`POIHSSFFuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m run was exhibiting unexpected behavior [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen reading BIFF records via `RecordInputStream`. A patch was attempted to “prime”[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe first record and adjust the implementations of `[0m[1;35mavailable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mhasNextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. When applied, the patch introduced widespread Java syntax [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merrors—primarily “illegal start of type” errors—due to misaligned or unclosed [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJavadoc comments and misplaced code insertions. The build now fails at dozens of [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocations within `RecordInputStream.java`.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m− A Jazzer/libFuzzer harness exercises the [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.poi.hssf.record.RecordInputStream` class in Apache POI.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m− The logs show normal instrumentation of many POI classes but no explicit crash; [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrather, it appears that `RecordInputStream` never progresses properly into record [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpotentially an infinite loop or zero-length reads[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m− Key symptom: `[0m[1;35mavailable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mhasNextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` may both return non-progressing [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalues [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `[0m[1;35mavailable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` returns zero when data hasn’t been primed[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, preventing [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madvancement through the BIFF stream.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mImportant Observations  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m− The field `_currentDataLength` is initialized to `DATA_LEN_NEEDS_TO_BE_READ` [0m[1;39m([0m[39ma [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msentinel[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m only when a new record is started, but the initial constructor paths do [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnot prime that first record.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m− As a result, `[0m[1;35mavailable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` may return zero at the stream’s outset, and [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mhasNextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` may throw or signal no further records.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m− The intended fix is to set `_currentDataLength` to the sentinel immediately in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe constructor and call `[0m[1;35mnextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` once if a valid SID is already read, so [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat reading methods see a real data length.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m− Removed the Javadoc comment before the `_currentDataLength` field declaration, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpresumably to adjust the comment layout.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m− In each constructor, after reading `_nextSid`, inserted:[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    * `_currentDataLength = DATA_LEN_NEEDS_TO_BE_READ;`[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    * `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m_nextSid != INVALID_SID_VALUE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35mnextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m− Overrode `[0m[1;35mavailable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m when `_currentDataLength` is the sentinel.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m− Modified `[0m[1;35mhasNextRecord[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to drop its `throws LeftoverDataException` and change [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe condition to check against the sentinel constant.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m− Compilation fails in `RecordInputStream.java` with ~[0m[1;36m200[0m[39m errors like “illegal [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstart of type”, “[0m[32m';'[0m[39m expected”, and “class, interface, or enum expected”.  [0m         [2m                [0m
